advancements.filched.aspect.filcher.root: An elusive creature adept at hiding both itself and its belongings.
aspect.filched.filcher.bug.description: They are sensitive to the Bane of Arthropods enchantment and have less health along with less reach.
aspect.filched.filcher.description:
Small elusive beings capable of slipping between spaces and vanishing into a private pocket realm known as Limbo.
While ideal for hiding their stolen treasures, this unstable dimension threatens to consume them if they wander too far.
aspect.filched.filcher.limbo_attuned.des:
While in Limbo, they are bigger, but get extra armor, reach and mining speed. If they crouch in Limbo, they can reduce their size even more then outside of limbo!
Additionally it seems that Limbo has less effect on them? They can survive easier there then others.
aspect.filched.filcher.unusual_shape.des:
Their body is an oddity, they are smaller, burn for longer and mine slower.
It's as-if they do not belong here...
block.minecraft.bed.limbo_too_uneasy: You may not rest now; you feel too uneasy around here
death.attack.lost_to_limbo.item: %1$s was lost to Limbo trying to escape %2$s using %3$s
death.attack.lost_to_limbo.player: %1$s was lost to Limbo trying to escape %2$s
Have a Wasted curse your Equipment
Exposes the weared to the elements of Limbo, without protection.
Wearer will be reshaped into something else if worn for too long...
item.filched.faded_relic.filcher.lore_2: This was not just The End...
item.filched.focus.filcher.use_condition: When used in Off Hand while Crouching in Limbo:
item.filched.focus.filcher.use_result_1: Enter or Exit Limbo along with another nearest mountless entity
item.filched.focus.filcher.use_result_2: Pick Up or Place Down your Filcher Anchor
item.filched.shattered_relic.filcher.lor: A taste of Limbo was felt for a moment...
Maybe, just maybe it was The Void...
config.filched.filcher.limbo_generation_: Determines the range in blocks which new Filcher locations are picked when trying to enter Limbo for the first time or without an active Filcher Anchor.
(10000 means a random location between 10000 and -10000 will be picked; Setting this to low values can have unstable results)
